    helpText: 'Finding a qualified mental health professional who understands the complexities of grief can provide crucial support for navigating the emotional challenges of loss. Look for licensed therapists with specific training in grief counseling, trauma therapy, or bereavement support, checking their credentials and reading reviews from other clients. Contact 2-3 potential therapists to discuss their approach, availability, and whether they accept your insurance, as having professional guidance can significantly improve your healing process and help you develop healthy coping strategies.'
